views.text:
Polallie Ridge, they could never make me hate you! The description and reviews say things like “underwhelming views” and “butt buster with no views” but we disagree! The first few miles you get to walk through some very nice open forest with lots of rocky outcroppings and it's pretty. And after that you get so many glimpses of the nearby mountains and valleys and they are gorgeous! Just because it’s not a knife edge 360 panoramic view the whole way doesn't mean there are no views in my book.

While the trail grade wasn't a walk in the park, it was no staircase either. There was no snow until after the wilderness boundary, after which the trail slowly turned into a big snowfield. We didn't need any traction devices (our sneakers+a lil kickstep did just fine) and we didn’t have trouble wayfinding but it would be good to have a map or app. The lake wasn't frozen, but the fish weren't biting. All in all we had a great hike and it was good to grease the knees for summer!

Flora and fauna: Deer tracks in the snow, tanagers, woodpeckers, pine siskins, townsends solitaire, grouse, a rufous hummingbird. The wildflowers were poppin off in the lower-mid elevations and the glacier lilies look about to bust at the top. Found some hooker's onion too.
